4 SJR___ CELEBRATING THE 150TH ANNIVERSARY OF GARDENDALE FIRST
5 BAPTIST CHURCH.
6
7 WHEREAS, highest commendations and congratulations
8 are herein proudly presented to Gardendale First Baptist
9 Church on the momentous occasion of its 150th Anniversary;
10 and
11 WHEREAS, Gardendale First Baptist Church has survived
12 throughout the years by the commitment of its pastors and
13 members and by the loving grace of God; many generations of
14 members have been encouraged and their faith strengthened
15 through the leadership of this church; it has grown into a
16 beacon of unselfish love and compassion for the community;
17 and
18 WHEREAS, in 1876, under the leadership of the
19 church's first pastor of record, Elder James Grimes, a group
20 of believers established a permanent place of worship known
21 as Chalybeate Springs Baptist Church, with an initial
22 membership of 27; and
23 WHEREAS, the congregation moved to Main Street, now
24 the Lighthouse Building, in 1914, and three years later the
25 church changed its name to Gardendale First Baptist Church;
26 and
27 WHEREAS, over the ensuing years, successive pastors
28 provided leadership that strengthened and improved the
Page 1

provided leadership that strengthened and improved the
SJR40 INTRODUCED
29 church family; and
30 WHEREAS, in 1934, Reverend C. B. Phillips became the
31 church's first full-time pastor, followed by Howard Bryant
32 in 1961, Lewis Marler in 1970, David Dykes in 1984, and
33 Steve Gaines in 1991; and
34 WHEREAS, the church has experienced steady growth and
35 stability, along with improvements and purchases that have
36 supported its ministries; and
37 WHEREAS, following the guidance of the Holy Spirit,
38 Dr. Kevin Hamm was installed as pastor in 2006, and under
39 his leadership the church has grown to a membership of more
40 than 6,000, drawing members from Jefferson County and the
41 surrounding areas; and
42 WHEREAS, in 2010, the church moved to its present
43 location alongside Interstate 65 in Gardendale and has
44 become known as the "church with the cross," referring to
45 the 125-foot cross visible from the interstate, which
46 represents God's love to the hundreds of thousands of people
47 who pass by each year; and
48 WHEREAS, the church remains committed to four core
49 values that guide the church's ministry to focus on
50 fostering a relationship with Christ, community, and
51 outreach: Worship God, Make Disciples, Love People, and
52 Share Jesus; and
53 WHEREAS, with the help of its dedicated congregation
54 and the leadership of its pastors through the years,
55 Gardendale First Baptist Church has faithfully shared the
56 Word and love of God, strengthened lives, and brought people
Page 2

Word and love of God, strengthened lives, and brought people
SJR40 INTRODUCED
57 together in fellowship and worship for 150 years; now
58 therefore,
59 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
60 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Gardendale First Baptist
61 Church is highly commended and celebrated on its milestone
62 150th Anniversary, and this resolution is offered to its
63 pastor and congregation in deepest admiration and
64 appreciation, along with sincere best wishes for continued
65 blessings.
